comment: this form is a unstressed prefix with kin terms for father, mother and older sibling; it is a free, stressed determiner with other lexical items

hi- is used with a limited set of lexical items (kin terms: father, mother, older sibling); it is alos only segmentally homophonous to 1.sg possessive, since when they overlap, the 3rd person form is a separate functional word, and the 1st person is a prefix
